Case No. 13,822. The TELLER. District Court, 1839. Maritime Liens — Repairs and Supplies — Home Port. [Cited in Thomas v. The Kosciusko, Case No. 13.9Ó1, and Ben. Adm. 162, to the point that the general maritime law does not provide a lien for supplies and labor furnished a vessel at her home port, since, in the absence of state regulation, such supplies and labor are presumed to have been furnished upon the personal credit of the owner of the vessel.]

[Nowhere reported; opinion not now accessible. Affirmed by circuit court; opinion not reported.]
